    "created_at": "2012-06-28T23:22:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-06-28T23:23:34Z",
    "body": "96 is ASCII for backtick. The culprit is libsyntax/parse/lexer.rs:695:next_token_inner.\n\nAll the error messages there are bad, and what's more, the span seems to be off-by-one (note where the arrow points):\n\n```\nparse-error.rs:2:18: 2:19 error: unknown character escape: 3232\nparse-error.rs:2     #error[\"%c.%c\", '\\\u0ca0', '\\\u0ca0'];\n                                   ^\n```\n\nNot gonna touch it myself, for fear that the int-ness is because of some unicode issue.\n",
