    "created_at": "2012-06-29T18:39:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-08-08T22:07:27Z",
    "body": "It seems to me that anything that's (a) on a standard keyboard layout and (b) part of ASCII 0-127 (notably, backquote) should be explicitly handled, because those are characters likely to be typed accidentally.\n\nGood catch on the off-by-one span. \n",
